The filter bubble discus the social media's effects and what the internet hidden from us as a consumers.
He - Eli Parriser - begins to explain how the filter bubble works and was formed.
When we use the internet we officially give the others to know our personal informations and its dangerous more than we imagine, the internet websites use our information to control the information we consume.
The internet and all the social media websites like Facebook, Instagram, Tweeter works in the filter bubble's way all the  websites were able to take your personal data and use this data to learn about you and then filter your results to what computer algorithms thought to believe reflected the real you and sell this information to companies to also advertise to your tastes.
The main idea of the article is that  the websites we visit are increasingly tailoring themselves to us by using our personal informations and it’s a dangerous thing that maybe put us in many complicated problems.